stiff records is a british independent record label formed in london, england, by dave robinson and jake riviera. originally active from 1976 to 1986, the label was reactivated in 2007. established at the outset of the punk rock boom, stiff records signed various punk and new wave acts such as nick lowe, the damned, lene lovich, wreckless eric, plummet airlines, elvis costello, ian dury and devo.